    • Method Detail

      • getSignature

        String getSignature()
        Function signature in a form of "name(type...)". Name is a literal that does not start with number and contains no control characters, which can be confused with SQL language punctuation. Control characters include but not limited to: ',', '(', ')', '*', '/', '%', '+', '-', '='.

        Argument types are represented by single character from this table:

        • B = byte
        • E = short
        • I = int
        • L = long
        • F = float
        • D = double
        • S = string
        • A = char
        • K = symbol
        • T = boolean
        • M = date
        • N = timestamp
        • U = binary
        • V = variable argument list
        • R = record
        • H = long256
        Lower-case letters will require arguments to be constant expressions. Upper-case letters allow both constant and variable expressions.
        Returns:
        signature, for example "substr(SII)"
